				The day my paladin looses to a SK is the day a ranger can tank better than a warrior.<BR>
<BR>
With high unbuffed  resists ( and cmon..like your gonna have AT LEAST 50 for all of em ..and thats not even with uber gear on ) AND with the paladins UBER resist desease poison and magic buffs up, AS IF ANY of an SK's measly spells are gonna hold LET ALONE the darkness series. I know it works both ways...SK's will most likely resist all of the pallies stuns..But an SK cannot Resist a paladin healing his/herself can he/she??..NO...sure they may get lucky with bash, but if they arnt using a 2hs'ing weapon than they'll have no chance of winning even if ALL their bashes land ( 2hs weapons far out damage a 1hs weapon and a sheild . )..( well assuming the paladin isnt stupid and is using a 2hs his/herself )<BR>
<BR>
SK pet doing decent damage? thats a myth!! besides...pop a Spook undead/Fol on the sucker and itll be out of the ball game for a while.<BR>
<BR>
AND, a DECENT pally will always leave two or more buff spaces open BEFORE his/her uber hp/ac buffs...this way they can cancel the SK's dots ( IF they do hold ) with cancel magic.<BR>
<BR>
In summary<BR>
<BR>
Paladins buffs+heals+Lay hands &gt; Sk's HT + easily resisted dots debuffs + pet<BR>
<BR>
Veinoras Angelfury 55 paladin
