	<tr>
		
			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				Now in all fairness, it can be argued that a smart pally can stand a chance agaist an SK. For giggles, let us asume that the SK is a human, erudite or DE just because the idea of ANY pally taking on an ogre or troll with in 1 or 2 lvls higher or lower is rediculous.<BR>
<BR>
Note this strategy works best in a nice open dueling area ;):<BR>
<BR>
First, make a pet and equip him with a pair of daggers.. 3 damage or 13, he will still do his max, mine is around 40 or so per hit (lvl 52 pet).<BR>
To ban the pet from fighting is like banning a rogue from back stabbing. Besides, where is it written that SKs fight fair?! <BR>
<BR>
Remember that lil spell called shadow step!? Open with that, this way you can confuse our lil prince valiant and get a couple good spells in before he finds where they are coming from, this is the perfect time to dark him, you see, even if he does catch on he will be too slow to effectively come after you before you can hit him with a dot or 2. next fear him... as it was discussed below, his cancel magic is useless if he has any buffs on what so ever, and they always will, its all they have. as he is running, walk up behind and beat the ever living bajeeezus out of him as rear attacks do the most damage. You will also have jolly Xabobin begin him cackling wickedly and hitting relentlessly. <BR>
<BR>
Repeat as needed! When he gets to about 1/3rd life is a good time to HT, many pallies will stay their LoH until the last minute, otherwise its wasted. My HT does well over 800pts of damage which is certain death to just about any pally that hurt.<BR>
<BR>
To be honest, the only time a pally is EVER gonna be competitive is when he has better gear. Come to think of it, ANY class can boast that. But get an SK and PAL together with equal equipment and I guarantee I know who the winner is gonna be hands down.<BR>
<BR>
The only other dueling race/class that has proven challenging is an Ogre warrior. They are TOUGH. As a matter of fact, the strongest player on 7th hammer is a lvl 60 ogre warrior named Klub, ofcoarse he looks like a DE most of the time due to his nifty pre-nerfed all/all Mask of Deception. He also has a full suit of orginal Rubicite, Cobalt, and other goddies. NASTY NASTY MAN, dont mess with him...:)
				</font>
			</td>

	</tr>
	
