			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				I don't know about that. As far as cancel magic goes, it always begins with the first thing cast on the player. <BR>
<BR>
So and &quot;smart&quot; pally will naturally buff up a bit before the big fight so he can be around 200hp short of my troll with around 40 or so points more sta naturally than mr half elf. <BR>
<BR>
What he will find is that he will have to cancel ALL of his precious buffs before he can even lay a hand on my 300pt snare DoT, let alone my other debuffs...<BR>
<BR>
As for fear, well, I am convinced that has ALOT to do with one's charisma..the lower the better. Mine is 15, due to this mask I got off an Iksar in LoIO (-25 cha). Beyond that, you cant cast or attack while feared...all you can do is run run run!<BR>
<BR>
As for this &quot;smart&quot; pally friend of yours, im sure you hold your RL friend in good regards, I have a friend that also plays a puss-&lt;cough&gt;pally... And I can tell you, beyond him I have yet to see ANY pally that can stand toe to toe with my TSK. to begin with, his natural str was 130, but I decided to put 10 more points into it after the SoL expansion. Since I regen 6 point per tick naturally, I decided to go also with both regen upgrades, giving me a grand total of 12 points per tick. <BR>
<BR>
Lets face it, there is no way in hell a half elf or dwarf could ever compete with a troll or ogre physically, and since barbies are the next best thing, it is even more unfortunate that they cant be pallies!<BR>
<BR>
Now I have been challeged, and took out more pallies than I have fingers to count on and NEVER lost to any of them! So I can tell you this comment is not theory but time tested facts. <BR>
Lets face it, this game has some RP aspects of it that shape each class for a specific purpose. The SK's job is to kill, the pallies to defend. They each excell wonderfully in their respective areas of occupation, but since the pally was not meant to fight like an SK, he will always loose to the better killer, for no NPC will ever be as Clever as a player, the only thing that allows them to beat us is numbers and dmg/hp ratio being ungodly higher, and I understand the reasoning behind that too.<BR>
<BR>
After all, if they weren't so tough, there would be no reason for 30 players to after them at a time :) making the EQ world a bit less colorful
